# Sentinel Shield — Semgrep scope for Laravel (+ Filament) projects.
# Copy to your repository ROOT as `.semgrepignore`. Semgrep reads it from the scan
# root, so the Sentinel Shield workflows run Semgrep with `-w /src` (repo root).
#
# SCOPE: this file affects SEMGREP / SAST ONLY. It does NOT change:
#   composer audit · npm audit · Trivy (fs/deps) · Syft SBOM · Gitleaks · Hadolint
# Those still scan dependencies, lockfiles, the whole tree, and the Dockerfile.
# (See docs/semgrep-scoping.md.)
#
# Goal: scan application code (app/, Modules/, resources/js, routes/, config/);
# do NOT treat vendored/generated/cache assets as application code.

# PHP dependencies + framework runtime
vendor/
storage/
bootstrap/cache/

# JS toolchain + build output
node_modules/
public/build/
public/hot
dist/
build/
coverage/

# Published / compiled vendor front-end assets (NOT your source)
public/vendor/
public/js/filament/
# Uncomment if you publish more vendor JS/CSS under public/ that you do not author:
# public/js/
# public/css/

# Do NOT exclude your application source — keep resources/js, app/, Modules/ scanned.
